data.title: Fidelity boosts Solana (SOL) ETF with 0.25% fee amidst rising institutional interest, as inflows surge and competition grows.
data.description: Fidelity has recently revised its Solana ETF filing by including a 0.25% fee, reflecting the increased attention towards Solana's blockchain capabilities. This move comes amidst a surge in market investments and the emergence of new competitors. These developments highlight the escalating interest in Solana, with the fee adjustment signaling Fidelity's strategic positioning in this space. The growing interest in Solana is evident through the substantial inflows and heightened competition within the market, underscoring its potential for widespread adoption and investment growth.

data.title: Michael Saylor faces challenges in Bitcoin Treasury industry growth due to traditional credit industry views, proposes solutions.
data.description: Michael Saylor, Executive Chairman of Strategy (NASDAQ: MSTR), discussed challenges hindering growth in the Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) treasury industry during the company's third-quarter earnings call. He mentioned that Bitcoin not being recognized as capital by traditional credit ratings agencies is a major obstacle. Saylor emphasized the importance of classifying Bitcoin as collateral and assigning it collateral value under conventional banking, insurance, and credit rating rules. This structural problem is impacting BTC accumulation and the industry. Saylor believes that overcoming these hurdles will be crucial for the growth of the company and the wider Bitcoin treasury sector. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Mastermind of $31M crypto scam arrested in Thailand, accused of orchestrating Ponzi scheme across Asia. Significant breakthrough in fraud investigations.
data.description: Law enforcement officials in Thailand have captured Liang Ai-Bing, the alleged mastermind behind a cryptocurrency Ponzi scheme that spanned across Asia and involved a staggering $31 million. This arrest represents a major development in the ongoing efforts to crack down on fraudulent activities in the crypto space.

data.title: Corbus Pharma prices public offering of 4.7M shares at $13/share, pre-funded warrants at $12.9999, totalling $75M.
data.description: Today, Corbus Pharmaceuticals Holdings, Inc. (Nasdaq: CRBP) based in NORWOOD, Mass., disclosed the details of its recent public offering. The company priced 4,744,231 shares of its common stock at $13.00 per share, generating proceeds of approximately $75 million, excluding expenses. Additionally, pre-funded warrants for 1,025,000 shares were offered to select investors at $12.9999 per warrant, with an exercise price of $0.0001 per share. To give a further boost, the underwriters were granted an option to purchase up to 865,384 more shares. The entire offering, consisting of shares and warrants, is anticipated to be finalized around November 3, 2025.

data.title: Nxera Pharma received manufacturing approval amendment for QUVIVIQ® 25 and 50mg in Asia, originally launched in Japan for chronic insomnia. Taiwan approval pending, Phase 3 trials in S. Korea.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Nxera Pharma Co., Ltd. shared that its subsidiary, Nxera Pharma Japan Co., Ltd., obtained a manufacturing approval partial amendment for QUVIVIQ® (daridorexant) 25 and 50 mg in Japan. Daridorexant, the active ingredient of QUVIVIQ®, was introduced in Japan as a treatment for chronic insomnia in December 2024. The Company is currently waiting for regulatory approval in Taiwan and is in the Phase 3 trial stage in South Korea. Nxera Pharma Co., Ltd. is listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol 4565.

data.title: Marimekko's Q3 net sales up 8% to EUR 50.8M & operating profit at EUR 12.5M. Jan-Sep net sales at EUR 134.8M. Full story: Benzinga.com.
data.description: Marimekko Corporation's interim report for January to September 2025 reveals positive growth in net sales and operating profit. In the third quarter, net sales increased by 8% to EUR 50.8 million, with operating profit reaching EUR 12.5 million. For the overall period, net sales grew by 5% to EUR 134.8 million, and operating profit improved to EUR 23.1 million. International sales saw significant growth, with wholesale and retail sales both increasing. The company projects net sales for 2025 to surpass the previous year, targeting a 16-19% operating profit margin. However, global trade policy shifts and market uncertainties pose risks. Key figures include a 8% growth in international sales for Q3 2025 and a 12% increase in EBITDA. Operating profit margin for Q3 2025 was at 24.6%, higher than the previous year. Further details available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Data breach at Conduent Business Services, LLC exposes 10.5 million records; under investigation.
data.description: A law firm based in San Francisco, Schubert Jonckheer & Kolbe LLP, is currently looking into a data breach incident that resulted in the unauthorized exposure of confidential data belonging to 10,515,849 individuals associated with clients of Conduent Business Services, LLC. The breach is being investigated following the incident, which occurred in New Jersey.

data.title: Aker Solutions had strong 3Q results in 2025, with revenues expected to surpass NOK 60 billion.
data.description: Norwegian company Aker Solutions showed robust growth and profitable margins in the third quarter of 2025. Significant progress was achieved in various projects during this period, contributing to the company's positive performance. Anticipated revenues for 2025 are now projected to surpass NOK 60 billion, reflecting the company's strong position in the market.
